text: Cambria County is a county located in the U.S. state of Pennsylvania. As of the 2020 census, the population was 133,472. Its county seat is Ebensburg. It was named for the nation of Wales, which in Latin is known as "Cambria". ==References== Category:1800s establishments in Pennsylvania Category:1807 establishments in the United States Category:Pennsylvania counties
title: Cambria County, Pennsylvania
